('49911','C001FC1MHM','76803952a','','birch_thinline','all','rail','all','all','','http://imerrow.com/nebula/inventory/rail/birch_closeup.jpg','','','','','','','','','','all','72157607111896150','72157625004387858','','','','<p class="p1">Rail Sewing Systems are designed for the 70/72-class line of butt-seaming machines.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>These systems automate the seaming of piece goods or fabric bolts for the great increases in productivity.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>The Rail delivers the straightest, most perfectly matched seam by aligning, matching and locking fabric ends before sewing begins. It features a positive carriage and head drive which maintains the rate of feed built into the machine, yet allows change of feed rate whenever necessary.</p>
<p class="p1">Other features of the rail system include friction wheel carriage drive, and sewing machine swing-out for adjustment or needle looper changes. The AC variable speed drive permits stitch or stitch multiplier changes at will.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Metal-sensing proximity switches replace the old mechanical limit switches, a vast improvement over traditional rail systems.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>All of the old belts, pulleys, clutches, rack gears and carriage wheels are a thing of the past, meaning fewer wear parts in your rail assembly.<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span></p>
<p class="p1">The Rail system is offered with a choice of selvedge clamps or pins.</p>
<p> For more information about the railways contact us at sales@merrow.com </p>

