igured to sew specifically using customers'' unique material and thread.  Tension settings, eccentrics, and cutter placement are all adjusted to ensure that the customer receives a unique version of the ActiveSeam that is specific to their garment and application. ','<b>NEW!!!</b>\r\nThe Merrow MB-4DFO 2.0 is used in cut and sew factories the world over to sew the ActiveSeam on technical fabrics and base layer garments.  Merrow''s worldwide network of authorized agents are trained in all aspects MB-4DFO 2.0 service and installation.','','','','72157627384626179','','A1DF','A00DF - A2DF','EXC-302-26','6-82-7','99','120','ACTIVESEAM','','','','','','','','','3450 RPM, 110/220 volt, 1/2HP ','','','','The Merrow MB-4DFO 2.0 sews all three versions of ActiveSeam - Infused, Comfort, and Slim.  ActiveSeam is an alternative for flatlock.','flatlock, flat lock, flat overlock, activeseam, infused stitch, comfort stitch, slim stitch, infused seam, comfort seam, slim seam, merrow, flat merrow, patagonia stitch, capilene stitch, merrow activeseam,two needle flat seam, mb-4dfo 2.0, blue merrow, mb4dfo, mb series, merrow mb, mb 4dfo 2.0, stretch seam, stretch stitch','The Merrow MB-4DFO 2.0 is a two-needle flat overlock serger that sews ActiveSeam.  ActiveSeam is a replacement for flatlock stitching on athletic garments and active wear.','flatlock, flat lock, flat overlock, activeseam, infused stitch, comfort stitch, slim stitch, infused seam, comfort seam, slim seam, merrow, flat merrow, patagonia stitch, capilene stitch, merrow activeseam,two needle flat seam, mb-4dfo, blue merrow, mb4dfo, mb series, merrow mb, mb 4dfo 2.0, stretch seam, stretch stitch','The Merrow MB-4DFO 2.0 sews all three versions of ActiveSeam - Infused, Comfort, and Slim.  ActiveSeam is a replacement for flatlock.','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','',3950),(55,0,'70','','','4','',76793432,'no','HAND-HELD','INDUSTRIAL HAND-HELD BUTT SEAMING MACHINE','The Merrow Hand-Held Butt Seaming Machine allows the operator to sew a traditional butted seam from multiple locations and positions. It is the lightest and fastest hand-held serger available and will sew a variety of wovens, non-wovens, and even knits. ','handheldbuttseamer','20','','20 ft/min','1/8"','5/8"','','','Yes','Single Thread','1','4','1','Hand-Held, Portable Seaming','','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NbY8ua9wUOk','','The Merrow Hand-Held Butt-Seamer is an industrial piece of equipment that allows the operator to sew at multiple angles and positions and from multiple locations.  It offers true portability and unmatched maneuverability, filling the gaps left by stationary butt-seamers.  ','The Merrow Hand-Held sews at a brisk 20 ft./min (6m/min) and is a single thread machine with cutters.  Like all Merrow Butt-Seamers, it is a true serger and is affixed with fabric cutters to ensure that material is seamed smoothly and in a straight line.  It weighs a paltry 8.75 lbs (~4kg) and if necessary can be suspended from a weight absorber. ','The Hand-Held sews a wide 5/8" butted seam on wovens, knits, and lightweight non-woven material.  Like all Merrow butt-seamers, it sews a uniform and flat stitch and won''t lap or bunch material within the seam.','The Merrow Hand-Held is used for any application requiring a butted-seam; it is frequently used at the end of a continuous process to repair damaged or skipped seams.  Although it is broadly used throughout the textile industry, its appeal extends to any industry where material is seamed as part of a continuous process. ','','','','72157607111896150','500133','10 S','10 S','','','','','501','','','','','','','','','None','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','',0),(58,0,'70','','','','',76804632,'yes','12-E','HEAVY DUTY JOINING','The 12-E is an American-made work horse meant for one thing - joining tough materials. Built to our strict manufacturing standards using robust parts and heavy-duty steel, the 12-E is designed to handle difficult to sew materials and heavy workloads.','12e','20','','1600 rpm','4 - 12 SPI','5/8"','','','','1','1','2','2','The NEW Merrow 12-E','Threading the 12-E','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WYFPsfeLqqI','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5tLecLkVt8A&feature=share&list=PLDhFBVs6UczuJ2_aX4GT9RiqGHGNm8jSz','The 12-E is an extra-high lift, single needle, single row sewing machine that joins tough material. It sews a 5/8" butted-seam at 1600 rpm.','The 12-E is constructed of robust parts and is built to Merrow''s rigid quality standards. The long arm design and high looper/needle throw provide the clearance required when seaming rigid materials, while the 6" hand wheel and plain feed 1/4" looper gauge provide the torque and strength necessary to penetrate thick material. ','The 12-E produces the wide, flat butted seam favored when joining material.  It sews a 5/8" butted-seam that is nearly as flat as the material itself, ensuring that subsequent processing equipment will not be affected as with other bulkier stitches.  ','The 12-E is used in typical textile joining applications and will join everything from carpet to leather. It is adept at seaming tough composites like kevlar, heavy duty carbon fiber, and fiberglass, and is the machine of choice for joining turf and other geotextiles. ','Butt-Seaming','','','72157629836062890','','11S','10S, 11S ','14-649','14-617','n/a','n/a','501','','','','','','','','','1725 RPM, 60 Hz, 1/2 HP, 110 or 220 volts, 1 or 3 phase','','','','Merrow 12-E Heavy Duty Joining Machine','butt-seaming, heavy duty seaming, end-to-end joining, 12e, 12 class, merrow black mamba','','','','Merrow','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','',5199),(56,0,'70','','mgbc','4','',76793432,'no','ULTRALIGHT','ULTRA-LIGHT INDUSTRIAL CHAIN STITCH MACHINE','The Merrow Ultra-Light is an astonishingly light, six pound industrial chain stitch machine - half the weight of similar machines.  The Ultra-Light is ideal for portable seaming, bag-closing, and sewing applications.','ultralight','70','','49 FT/MIN.','','7MM (1/4")','','','','SINGLE THREAD','1','3','0','','','','','The Merrow UltraLight weights half as much as similar hand-helds (only six pounds), giving operators true portability and unmatched maneuverability.  The UltraLight can be used without the need for a weight absorber (though this is an option) and serves a multitude of applications.','The UltraLight is simple to thread and extremely easy to operate.  It sews an astounding 49 feet per minute, and will sew any manner of fabric or paper up to 1500 grams per square meter. ','The Merrow UltraLight sews a single thread 7mm (1/4") simple chain stitch.  The thread tension is easily adjustable to ensure the optimum balance between stitch security and removeability. ','The Merrow UltraLight is widely used for seaming and bag closing applications in the agriculture, animal feed, seed, pet food, chemical, mineral, milling, food, building material, medical and pharmaceutical industries.  ','','','','','','10 S',' 10 S','','','','','401','','','','','','','','','None','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','',0),(59,0,'72','','','8','',76803782,'yes','71-1D-2','HIGH SPEED DRY SEAMING','The 71-Class is a NEW addition to the Merrow machine lineup. It replaces the outgoing 70-1D models and is available as a NEW painted model - the 71-1D-2 - as well as the traditional nickel plated version.  The 71-Class is a high speed butt seamer that runs at 4000 rpm and sews a 3/8" wide stitch.','711d2','70','','4000','101MM - 305MM (4-12 SPI)','6.4MM (3/8")','','','','1-2','1','0','0','Sewing on the 71-1D-2','','','','The 71-1D-2 is a NEW, single needle, one-thread, double row feed butt-seamer that runs on Merrow''s barrel cam architecture. It joins DRY, light to medium weight KNIT fabric at HIGH SPEED.  With minimal part upgrades, the 71-1D-2 can easily be converted to sew with two threads.','The 71-1D-2 is a hybrid of Merrow''s MG-Class and 70-Class machines. While the 71-Class sews with the precision and speed of our MG overlock models, it does not recirculate oil and prevents the internal buildup of particulates that plagues self-oiling machines. All 71-Class models have specially milled cam grooves that allow consistent, uninterrupted sewing at up to 4000 rpm.\r\n','The combination of high speed sewing and a narrower butted seam makes the 71-1D-2 ideal for seaming lightweight knits. It sews a flat and strong stitch that is similar to the traditional Merrow butt seam, but at 3/8" is tighter and more compact, creating a secure joint on lightweight fabric. The 71-Class stitch still maintains a flat profile however, and will not interfere with subsequent finishing processes. ','The 71-1D-2 is engineered for dry industrial environments where fast seaming of knit fabric is required. Because it does not recirculate oil it offers a distinct advantage over converted overlock machines, and like all Merrows it is designed to run continuously without interruption due to machine or stitch failure. ','','','','72157630065869593','500002','MERROW 6SDT','MERROW 3SDT - 8SDT ','','','','','501','','','','','','','','','3450 RPM, 110/220 volt, 1/2HP ','','','','','','','','','','http://marketing-downloads.s3.amazonaws.com/linecard_711d2.pdf','http://marketing-downloads.s3.amazonaws.com/tf_chart.pdf','','','','http://marketing-downloads.s3.amazonaws.com/711d2_linecard_icon.jpg','http://marketing-downloads.s3.amazonaws.com/tfchart_icon.jpg','','','','Download a Printable Linecard for the 71-1D-2','Download the Continuous Processing Comparison Chart!','','','',3445),(60,0,'72','','','8','',76804717,'yes','71-1D-2 CNP','HIGH SPEED WET SEAMING','The 71-1D-2 CNP is a completely nickel plated butt-seamer that is used for joining material in wet environments. It is a high speed sewing machine and sews a 3/8" wide tight butted seam on wet or dry goods. The 71-1D-2 CNP is ideal for light to medium weight knit material. ','711d2cnp','70','','4000','101MM - 305MM (4-12 SPI)','6.4MM (3/8")','','','','1-2','1','0','0','Sewing on the 71-1D-2 CNP','','','','The 71-1D-2 CNP is a chemically nickel plated, single needle, one-thread, double row differential feed butt-seamer that runs on Merrow''s barrel cam architecture. It joins WET or DRY, light to medium weight KNIT fabric at HIGH SPEED.  With minimal part upgrades, the 71-1D-2 CNP can easily be converted to sew with two threads.','The 71-1D-2 CNP is coated with a chemically adhered nickel plating which allows the machine to be used in wet or caustic environments where corrosion is a concern. It is a hybrid of Merrow''s MG-Class and 70-Class machines and while it sews with the precision and speed of our MG overlock models, it does not recirculate oil and prevents the internal buildup of particulates that plagues self-oiling machines. ','The combination of high speed sewing and a narrower butted seam makes the 71-1D-2 CNP ideal for seaming lightweight knits. It sews a flat and strong butt seam that is narrower than the traditional Merrow butt seam, but at 3/8" is tighter and more compact, creating a secure joint on lightweight fabric. The 71-Class stitch still has a flat profile however, and will not interfere with subsequent finishing processes. ','The 71-1D-2 CNP is used in wet industrial environments where fast seaming of knit fabric is required. The nickel plating makes the machine ideal for dye houses or facilities that specialize in bleaching, mercerising, washing, or printing.','','','','72157630194595902','500002','MERROW 6SDT','MERROW 3SDT - 8SDT ','','','','','501','','','','','','','','','3450 RPM, 110/220 volt, 1/2HP ','','','','','','','','','','http://marketing-downloads.s3.amazonaws.com/linecard_711d2cnp.pdf','http://marketing-downloads.s3.amazonaws.com/tf_chart.pdf','','','','http://marketing-downloads.s3.amazonaws.com/711d2cnp_linecard_icon.jpg','http://marketing-downloads.s3.amazonaws.com/tfchart_icon.jpg','','','','Download a Printable Linecard for the 71-1D-2 CNP','Download the Continuous Processing Comparison Chart!','','','',4495),(61,0,'72','','','8','',76804718,'yes','71-1D-7 CNP','HIGH SPEED WET SEAMING','The 71-1D-7 CNP is a high speed butt-seamer that has high lift cams for joining thicker knits. It sews a 3/8" flat butt seam at speed (up to 4000 rpm) and is completely nickel plated for use in harsh environments or when joining wet material.\r\n\r\n\r\n','711d7cnp','70','','4000','101MM - 305MM (4-12 SPI)','6.4MM (3/8")','','','','1-2','1','0','0','Sewing on the 71-1D-7 CNP','','','','The 71-1D-7 CNP is a high lift, chemically nickel plated butt-seamer that is used for joining medium weight wet or dry knits. It is a single needle, one thread, double row differential feed machine with cutters. ','The 71-1D-7 CNP has unique high lift cams, making it  suitable for sewing heavier knits. It is coated with a chemically adhered nickel plating which allows the machine to be used in wet or caustic environments where corrosion is a concern and it does not recirculate oil to prevent the internal buildup of particulates common in factory environments. ','The 71-1D-7 sews a flat and strong 3/8" stitch that is tighter and more compact than the traditional Merrow butt seam. The narrow width creates a strong joint on knit fabric, and the 71-1D-7 excels at seaming medium weight goods. With minimal part upgrades, the 71-1D-7 CNP can easily be converted to sew a two-thread seam.','The 71-1D-7 CNP is used in wet industrial environments where fast seaming of medium weight knit fabric is required. The nickel plating makes the machine ideal for dye houses or facilities that specialize in bleaching, mercerising, washing, or printing.','','','','72157630196213508','500002','MERROW 6SDT','MERROW 3SDT - 8SDT ','','','','','501','','','','','','','','','3450 RPM, 110/220 volt, 1/2HP ','','','','','','','','','','http://marketing-downloads.s3.amazonaws.com/linecard_711d7cnp.pdf','http://marketing-downloads.s3.amazonaws.c