('500001','300001','70-ADN-1','The sample you were viewing is a single thread rolled edge butted seam used in the continuous processing of loosely woven material.  A traditional flat seam was not able to hold the two pieces of fabric together.  The rolled edge creates a more secure stitch.  It can only be used when a flat stitch is not required.','The stitch is made by the Merrow 70-ADN-1.  This machine is designed for use with loose woven or knit fabric.  The loose structure of the fabric causes a traditional seam to pull out during processing.  ','This machine is currently supported by Merrow.  Spare parts are available in the Merrow Store.','This machine is not in current production.  It has been replaced by the Merrow 72-D3BR.','70-ADN-1'),
